title: ICE: associated type missing default with default impl

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: regression-from-stable-to-nightly
labels.description: Performance or correctness regression from stable to nightly.

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
I tried this code on nightly: ```rust trait X { type S; fn f() -> Self::S {} } fn main() {} ``` I expected to see this happen: Mismatched type error Instead, this happened: ``` error: internal compiler error: src/librustc_typeck/collect/type_of.rs:51: associated type missing default --> :7:5 | 7 | type S; | ^^^^^^^ ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.45.0-nightly (bad3bf622 2020-05-09) binary: rustc commit-hash: bad3bf622bded50a97c0a54e29350eada2a3a169 commit-date: 2020-05-09 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.45.0-nightly LLVM version: 9.0 ```
